---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<Base title="About — LYP" description="Learn about my mission to build freedom technology.">
  <div class="container">
    <article class="about-content prose">
      <h1>About</h1>

      <p class="lead">
        I'm a philosopher-builder focused on <strong>freedom technology</strong> — tools that make individuals more sovereign in an increasingly centralized digital world.
      </p>

      <h2>Mission</h2>
      <p>
        The internet promised to decentralize power. Instead, we've seen unprecedented concentration — of our data, our attention, our identities. A handful of companies now mediate most human connection and information flow.
      </p>
      <p>
        I believe technology should serve individuals, not extract from them. My work focuses on building and advocating for tools that restore personal agency across four dimensions:
      </p>

      <ul>
        <li><strong>Privacy</strong> — Your data belongs to you. Period.</li>
        <li><strong>Attention</strong> — Your focus is yours to direct, not harvest.</li>
        <li><strong>Ownership</strong> — True digital ownership without permission from intermediaries.</li>
        <li><strong>Truth</strong> — Verification and authenticity in an age of synthetic media.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What I'm building</h2>
      <p>
        I work on open-source tools, write about the philosophy of technology, and explore practical applications of cryptography, decentralized systems, and privacy-preserving computation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Check out my <a href="/projects">projects page</a> to see what I'm currently working on, or read my <a href="/blog">blog</a> for deeper dives into these ideas.
      </p>

      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        Technology is never neutral — it embeds the values of its creators. Code is law, in more ways than one. I believe we have both the opportunity and responsibility to build systems that expand human freedom rather than constrain it.
      </p>
      <p>
        This isn't about rejecting technology or returning to some pre-digital past. It's about being intentional. About building with sovereignty as a first principle rather than an afterthought.
      </p>

      <h2>Get in touch</h2>
      <p>
        I'm always interested in connecting with others who care about these ideas. Whether you're building something similar, have questions, or just want to discuss — reach out.
      </p>

      <div class="contact-links">
